body: Mostapha, I am having a few issues with the new userobject file from the GitHub. See images below. old version of gencumskyMtx [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/u1yFp6ePHh6-vfDLbRyamdxzuj1*G2BBvFCcRdn-3gKv9f8NItIUVdly7GAYcrV*1rj2Pn40lI1pqiTZhhJTkjaTvLUmZGR0/2015.01.25oldversion.jpg)     new version of GencumskyMtx[](http://api.ning.com:80/files/u1yFp6ePHh70aLhDYoPHfo8HL9iwGtlQ0mlzik*6HQuSndq2v5mHOu3nJMFulFvQFY-sU2Yor0O-k9af5Sfbfr5w-Q-qVLY9/2015.01.25newversion.jpg) There are two issues: 1: The cumulative sky dome viewer returns the error "sky type not found". It just recently changed to give me a runtime error, index out of range 144. 2: The selectSkyMtx object now returns all text, where before it returned text and number values. I can get around this issue using your ladybug split text/numbers module, but I thought it may lead to where the issue is. Any idea what is causing this?
